{
  "texts": [
    "For one, reproducibility is a major bottleneck 146.",
    "However, digital twins can excel at this, especially if built under an opensource framework.",
    "Additionally, organoids do not yet capture the entire physiological repertoire of cell types, or even the behavior that is relevant for a particular disease.",
    "This means, for instance, that the response to drugs or other interventions needs to be studied for organoids per se, separately from the in vivo target.",
    "They also have a relatively limited range of heterogeneity in responses, but a broader range is needed to develop truly personalized digital twins 146."
  ]
}